org.safs.control

Class ControlStep

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.safs.control.Control
      • org.safs.control.ControlStep
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Observer

    public class ControlStep
extends Control
implements java.util.Observer
    Description : ControlStep, used to control an engine by sending step commands
    Since:
    NOV 24, 2003
    NOV 24, 2003 (DBauman) Original Release, copied from RobotJHook.

    a controller for teststeps: if the arg is testscript, then it loads the file specifed and treats each line as a test script. If no args are specified, the it uses Class.forName to load the org.safs.control.swing.ControlStepUI class which is the Observable to our Observer. Our 'update' method gets the commands from that GUI and executes them

    Author:
    dbauman

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)

        Purpose: main method
        Parameters:
        args, - String[],
        NO ARGS: then try to load the GUI piece to do the control
        args[0]: can be:
        testscript: load step commands from file in args[1]
        guiname: load step commands from file in args[1]
        args[1]: if testscript, then args[1] is the filename
        args[1]: if guiname, then args[1] is the gui class name
        args[2]: if testscript, then args[2] can be:
        debug: show debug info
        nodebug: do not show debug info
        otherwise: use args[2] as the delimeter/separator in the step commands (default: ,)
